{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":109085,"duration_api_ms":61127,"num_turns":9,"result":"Both critical test-stub tests pass. Here is the JSON response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Seventh remediation round addressing 6 QA amendments: (1) Added clarifying doc comment at the OPENROUTER_API_KEY check site explaining BinaryNotFound is repurposed as a terminal 'infrastructure prerequisite missing' signal, and added a doc comment on the BinaryNotFound enum variant itself documenting its broader scope. (2) Restored exit code 127 → BinaryNotFound classification in classify_exit_failure: the function now matches on status.code() and maps Some(127) to BinaryNotFound (terminal), all other exits to TransportFailure (retryable). The _status parameter is now used. Updated the test to exit_code_127_returns_binary_not_found asserting BinaryNotFound. (3) Simplified backoff_for_attempt to compute the multiplier directly as 2u32.saturating_pow(attempt.saturating_sub(1)), eliminating the fragile u64→u32 conversion via try_into().unwrap_or(u32::MAX). (4) Fixed the service timeout +30s regression by adding an enforces_timeout() trait method to AgentExecutionPort (default false). ProcessBackendAdapter, TmuxAdapter, and OpenRouterBackendAdapter return true (they enforce their own inner timeout). The service now only adds the 30s buffer when enforces_timeout() is true; otherwise it uses request.timeout directly, restoring correct timeout behavior for stub and other lightweight adapters. (5) Exit 127 is now classified as BinaryNotFound (see item 2). (6) Fixed 3 engine availability rewrap sites (prompt-review refiner, final-review planner, final-review arbiter) to extract and preserve the original failure_class from BackendUnavailable errors instead of hardcoding failure_class: None, so BinaryNotFound from check_availability propagates correctly through panel dispatch.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel.\",\n    \"The BinaryNotFound failure class name is used for both missing binaries and missing API keys (OPENROUTER_API_KEY). Doc comments and inline comments now clarify this dual use as a general 'fatal infrastructure prerequisite' signal, but operator logs will still show 'binary_not_found' for missing env vars. A future rename to FatalInfrastructure would be clearer but requires broader codebase changes.\",\n    \"The pre-existing flaky test service_emits_invocation_completed_trace_with_token_fields occasionally fails under high parallelism due to tracing subscriber interference between tests. This is unrelated to our changes and passes reliably in isolation.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added enforces_timeout() trait method to AgentExecutionPort with default false. Implemented enforces_timeout() returning true for ProcessBackendAdapter, OpenRouterBackendAdapter, and TmuxAdapter (delegates to inner process adapter). Added enforces_timeout() delegation to the BackendAdapter enum. Updated service.rs to conditionally add the 30s buffer only when enforces_timeout() is true, restoring correct timeout behavior for stub and other non-timeout-enforcing adapters.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Restored exit code 127 → BinaryNotFound classification in classify_exit_failure: function now matches status.code() with Some(127) → BinaryNotFound and _ → TransportFailure. The previously unused _status parameter is now actively used. Updated doc comment to explain the 127 convention. Renamed test to exit_code_127_returns_binary_not_found and updated assertion to match BinaryNotFound.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Fixed 3 engine availability rewrap sites to preserve failure_class from the original error: prompt-review refiner (engine.rs:5954), final-review planner (engine.rs:6430), and final-review arbiter (engine.rs:6439) now extract failure_class from the inner BackendUnavailable error via pattern matching instead of hardcoding failure_class: None. Non-BackendUnavailable errors still default to None.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Simplified backoff_for_attempt: replaced 2u64.saturating_pow(...) with try_into().unwrap_or(u32::MAX) chain with direct 2u32.saturating_pow(attempt.saturating_sub(1)), eliminating the lossy u64→u32 conversion entirely.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added clarifying doc comment at the OPENROUTER_API_KEY check site in process_backend.rs explaining that BinaryNotFound is repurposed as a terminal 'infrastructure prerequisite missing' signal. Added doc comment on the BinaryNotFound enum variant in domain.rs documenting its broader scope beyond literal missing binaries.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified all 678 tests pass (cargo test), cargo clippy -- -D warnings clean, cargo fmt --check clean. Feature-gated verification: service_times_out_and_requests_backend_cancellation passes (timeout regression fixed), service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_transport_failure passes, exit_code_127_returns_binary_not_found passes.\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 678 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored across all test binaries\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences (exit 0)\",\n    \"service_times_out_and_requests_backend_cancellation (--features test-stub): passes — stub adapter with 100ms delay and 10ms timeout correctly times out at the service level because enforces_timeout() returns false, so service_timeout equals request.timeout (10ms) without the 30s buffer\",\n    \"service_returns_backend_unavailable_as_transport_failure (--features test-stub): passes — stub BackendUnavailable with failure_class: None correctly defaults to TransportFailure (retryable)\",\n    \"exit_code_127_returns_binary_not_found: passes — exit code 127 from a running process now correctly maps to BinaryNotFound (terminal), preventing wasted retry attempts on missing binaries\",\n    \"spawn_missing_binary_returns_binary_not_found: passes — spawn() ErrorKind::NotFound path produces BinaryNotFound\",\n    \"All retry_policy_test tests pass: default limits, exponential backoff with 2u32 multiplier capped at 60s, no_backoff returns zero\",\n    \"All 72 workflow_engine_test tests pass with --features test-stub: retry exhaustion (5 attempts), resume-from-failed (6 stage entries), cancellation during backoff, and preflight failure tests\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":0.7945975,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":91284,"cache_read_input_tokens":314295,"output_tokens":2676,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":91284,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":2676,"cacheReadInputTokens":314295,"cacheCreationInputTokens":91284,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7945975,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ff072e0e-74ca-4b9d-9500-abb87061f9d9"}
